New Records: Ruben Trumpelmann became the first player in T20I history to take two wickets with the first two balls of a match.
David Wiese contributed significantly with both batting and bowling performance.
Key Match Events: The match ended in a Super Over after both teams scored 109 runs each.
Namibia won the Super Over by scoring 21 runs, while Oman's response was insufficient.
Post-Match Reflections: Namibia's victory marked a significant milestone in their T20 World Cup campaign.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match featured the first Super Over in the T20 World Cup in 12 years.
